de.charite.compbio.jannovar.pedigree

Class GenotypeList

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.charite.compbio.jannovar.pedigree.GenotypeList
  • Deprecated. 
    Use VariantContextList instead

    @Deprecated
public final class GenotypeList
extends Object
    Wrapper for a immutable lists of Genotype calls for one TranscriptModel, one list of calls for each individual. This name list is used for ensuring that the same order and number of individuals is used in the genotype file as in the pedigree file.
    Author:
    Manuel Holtgrewe

        Construct and initialize object.
        Parameters:
        geneID - name of gene that this genotype list is for
        names - individual names, gives sorting of individuals in the call lists
        isXChromosomal - true if the gene list is on the X chromosome, only affects X-linked compatibility checks (setting this to true can lead to too false positives and but neither true nor false can lead to false negatives, given the filter's properties)
        calls - the genotype calls for this list

      • namesEqual

        public boolean namesEqual(Pedigree pedigree)
        Deprecated. 
        Check whether the names of this GenotypeList are the same as the names of the members of pedigree. For this, the order of the names has to be the same as the number of the names. This check is important for the PedigreeDiseaseCompatibilityDecorator, where the names in the pedigree must be the same as the names in the genotype list.
        Returns:
        true if the list of names is the same as the names of the members of pedigree
